## Hints for Future Agents
- AGENTS_global.md is the canonical single-file aggregation for tools that read
  AGENTS.md but do not support Claude Code's .claude/rules directory.
- install.sh now links AGENTS_global.md to both ~/.codex/AGENTS.md and
  ~/.pi/agent/AGENTS.md. If either tool's global context file seems stale,
  rerun install.sh or inspect those symlinks.
- Claude Code still uses the native rules directory via ~/.claude/rules -> repo
  rules/. Do not replace that with AGENTS_global.md unless the user explicitly
  asks; Claude Code's rules directory supports path scoping.
- AGENTS_global.md is generated by convention only. There is no checked-in
  generator script or install-time regeneration, so changes to rules/*.md must
  be manually re-concatenated into AGENTS_global.md unless future work adds
  automation.
- The gopls-lsp rule includes YAML frontmatter. In AGENTS_global.md this is
  preserved as text so non-Claude agents can see the intended scope, but it is
  not expected to be machine-enforced by pi.

## Codebase Discoveries
- install.sh is the central dotfiles setup script and uses direct symlinks from
  the repo into home-directory configuration locations.
- Pi loads global context from ~/.pi/agent/AGENTS.md, so no pi_settings.json
  change was required for global instructions.
- The repo already had AGENTS_global.md tracked as an empty file and already
  used it for Codex, making it the natural target for the concatenated rules.
- Recent commit history is mixed but mostly uses short capitalized imperative
  subjects rather than conventional commits, so this commit follows that style.

